# Next.js App Router

- Use App Router conventions throughout the project.
- Prefer Server Components by default.
- Add `"use client"` only when browser APIs, client state, or client-only libraries are required.
- Keep data fetching close to the route or server boundary when possible.
- Use route groups and nested layouts to keep the information architecture clean.
- Keep API route handlers focused and avoid mixing UI concerns into them.
- Put shared server utilities in `lib` or `src/lib`, not inside page files.
- Prefer streaming-friendly and cache-aware patterns when they improve responsiveness without hiding freshness tradeoffs.
